{"lemma":"حِبالَةٍ","slug":"حِبالَةٍ","root":"ح.ب.ل","root_slug":"ح-ب-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6983"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"snare, a net or other tied or tying thing by which one catches"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rope-making or the particular mode thereof"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħi.baː.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6983","headword_ar":"حِبَالَةٌ","root":"Hbl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHobuwlapN","text_ar":"اُحْبُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHobuwlN","text_ar":"اُحْبُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A snare;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing by means of which one takes, catches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"snares, game, or wild animals,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"birds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of whatever kind it be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arak","text_ar":"شَرَك"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HbAlp","text_ar":"حبالة"},{"kind":"text","text":"peculiarly applies to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cord"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habol","text_ar":"حَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of him who takes, catches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"snares, game or the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAy^ilu","text_ar":"حَبَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) and of the second [and third]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAbiylu","text_ar":"اَحَابِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$~i *uw^aAlapa biAlHibaAlapi","text_ar":"خَشِّ ذُوَالَةَ بِالحِبَالَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Frighten thou the wolf to catch him with the snare"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*w^Alp","text_ar":"ذوالة"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the wolf: applied to him whose threatening is not cared for: i. e., threaten another than me; for I know thee. (Meyd, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~isaA='u","text_ar":"النِّسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAy^ilu Al$~ayoTaAni","text_ar":"حَبَايِلُ الشَّيْطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Women are the snares of the Devil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAy^ilu Almawoti","text_ar":"حَبَايِلُ المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The causes of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa HibaAlapu AlA_ibili","text_ar":"هُوَ حِبَالَةُ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who takes good care of the camels, so that they do not escape from him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  For the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAy^ilu","text_ar":"حَبَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolN","text_ar":"حَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places; in the first sentence, and near the end of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Lth","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}